assistant_prompt:
Here's an example script that uses the Roblox Luau language to find the nearest character and teleport you to that character:

```
[Luau]

Description = The Luau script allows players to experience the fun and excitement of being a native Hawaiian at a luau party.

CharacterFinding = false

[Code]

function GetNearestCharacter(): Character {
    var characters = GetCharacter().getNearbyCharacters(10.0, CharacterFacing.All);

    if (characters.length > 0) {
        var nearestCharacter = characters[0];
        return GetNearbyCharacter(nearestCharacter).teleportTo();
    } else {
        return null;
    }
}

function GetNearbyCharacter(character: Character): Character {
    return GetCharacter().getCharacter(character.characterId, 10.0).getCharacter();
}

function TeleportToCharacter(character: Character) {
    return GetCharacter().teleportTo(character.characterId, CharacterFacing.All);
}

```

This script first sets the CharacterFacing property to All to allow the script to search for characters in all directions. Then, it uses the Character.getNearbyCharacters() function to search for nearby characters within a 10-meter radius. The function returns a CharacterCollection object that contains information about all the characters that are within 10 meters of the player. The function then selects the first character in the collection (the nearest character) and returns a Character object for that character using Character.getCharacter().

In the GetNearestCharacter() function, the code sets the CharacterFacing property to All to allow the script to search for characters in all directions. Then, it uses the Character.getNearbyCharacters() function to search for nearby characters within a 10-meter radius. The function returns a CharacterCollection object that contains information about all the characters that are within 10 meters of the player.

The function then selects the first character in the collection (the nearest character) and returns a Character object for that character using Character.getCharacter().

The GetNearbyCharacter() function is used to return the nearest character based on the distance from the player. The function uses the Character.characterId property to identify the character that the player is seeking and then uses the getCharacter() function to retrieve the character information for that character.

